{{Infobox organization | name = Academic and Research Network of Slovenia | abbreviation = ARNES | motto = Connecting knowledge | image = ARNES (Slovenia) Logo.gif | image_border = | size = | alt = ARNES Logo | formation = May 1992 | purpose = | headquarters = [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]] | status = Public institution | region_served = Slovenia | leader_title = Director | leader_name = Marko Bonač | main_organ = Board of Directors | website = {{URL|http://www.arnes.si/en}} }}
The '''Academic and Research Network of Slovenia''' ({{lang-sl|Akademska in raziskovalna mreža Slovenije}}) is a public [[institute]] in [[Slovenia]], established in May 1992. Its main task is development, operation and management of the communication and information network for [[education]] and [[research]]. ARNES also operates the [[Slovenian Internet Exchange]]. <ref name=ArnesAnniversaryTimes>{{cite news | title =ARNES network marking 25th anniversary | url=http://www.sloveniatimes.com/arnes-network-marking-25th-anniversary |publisher=The Slovenia Times | accessdate = 11 September 2016 |archive-date=11 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910224126/http://www.sloveniatimes.com/arnes-network-marking-25th-anniversary }}</ref> The members of its management board are appointed by the [[Government of Slovenia]]. <ref name=ArnesRtvSlo>{{cite web | title = Arnes - začetnik internetnih storitev, brez katerih danes ne gre več|trans-title=Arnes - pioneer of internet services, without which life is not imaginable nowadays |url=http://www.rtvslo.si/uspesna-slovenija/arnes-zacetnik-internetnih-storitev-brez-katerih-danes-ne-gre-vec/356747| accessdate = 24 August 2016 |archive-date=11 September 2017 |archive-url=http://www.rtvslo.si/uspesna-slovenija/arnes-zacetnik-internetnih-storitev-brez-katerih-danes-ne-gre-vec/356747 }}</ref> <ref name=SloInternetTimes>{{cite web | title=Slovenia Marks 20 Years of Internet Presence | url=http://www.sloveniatimes.com/slovenia-marks-20-years-of-internet-presence |publisher=The Slovenia Times | accessdate = 11 September 2017 |archive-date=11 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910225320/http://www.sloveniatimes.com/slovenia-marks-20-years-of-internet-presence }}</ref>
Also a part of ARNES, is [[SI-CERT]], the Slovenian [[Computer Emergency Response Team]]. It was established in 1994 and has been led by Gorazd Božič. SI-CERT was involved in the take-down of the recordings of the [[Government of Slovenia]]'s [[2011 Slovenian YouTube affair|closed session recordings leaked in December 2011 on YouTube]]. The recordings were taken down by YouTube after the copyright-related lawsuit threat by SI-CERT.<ref name="Siol27-1-2012">{{cite news |url=http://www.siol.net/novice/slovenija/2012/01/dostop_do_spective_so_imele_po_informacijah_kamnarjeve_tri_osebe.aspx |title=Dostop do Spective naj bi imele tri osebe |language=Slovenian |trans-title=Three Persons are Supposed to Had Access to Spectiva |newspaper=Planet Siol.net |publisher=TSmedia, medijske vsebine in storitve, d.o.o. |date=27 January 2012| archive-date=11 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910223522/http://siol.net/novice/slovenija/dostop-do-spective-naj-bi-imele-tri-osebe-231526 }}</ref> It has not been involved in the investigation of the leak.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dnevnik.si/novice/slovenija/1042505577 |title=Posnetki vladnih sej na portalu YouTube: Dostop naj bi imele zgolj tri osebe |language=Slovenian |trans-title=The Recordings of Government Sessions on the YouTube Portal: The Access Is Supposed to be Available to Only Three People |newspaper=Dnevnik.si |publisher=Dnevnik, d. d. |date=27 January 2012| archive-date=11 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910223842/https://www.dnevnik.si/1042505577/lokalno/1042505577 }}</ref>
