The '''European Federation of Krav Maga''' (FEKM for Fédération Européenne de Krav Maga in French) was founded in 1997 by Richard Douieb.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fekm-uk.com/about/the-fekm-rd/|title=The FEKM-RD - European Federation of Krav Maga - UK Sector|work=European Federation of Krav Maga - UK Sector|access-date=2017-04-04|language=en-US}}</ref> Richard has received the delegation of [[Imi Lichtenfeld]], the founder of [[Krav Maga]], to represent the discipline in Europe in 1987.  Since its creation, the FEKM has expanded in more than 12 countries around the world and counts 18 000 practitioners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://krav-maga.net|title=Fédération Européenne de Krav-maga|website=krav-maga.net|access-date=2017-04-04}}</ref>

