'''''Koštana''''' ''([[Serbian Cyrillic alphabet|Serbian Cyrillic]]: Коштана'') is a popular [[Play (theatre)|play]], written by [[Borisav Stanković]]. It is set in Stanković's native [[Vranje]], a town in southern [[Serbia]]. It features many themes of [[Serbia]]n [[folklore]] and patriarchal customs which were still present in the late nineteenth century. The play is very popular to this day.

The Serbian composer [[Petar Konjović]] wrote an [[opera]] of the same name based on the play.

