{{Infobox military installation | name = Saint Mary's Battery | native_name = Batterija ta' Santa Marija | location = [[Marsalforn]], [[Żebbuġ, Gozo|Żebbuġ]], [[Gozo]], [[Malta]] | image = | caption = | type = [[Artillery battery]] | coordinates = {{coord|36|4|32.7|N|14|15|27.4|E|type:landmark|display=inline}} | built = 1715 | used = | builder = [[Knights Hospitaller|Order of Saint John]] | materials = [[Limestone]] | height = | fate = Demolished | battles = | events = }}
'''Saint Mary's Battery''' ({{lang-mt|Batterija ta' Santa Marija}}), also known as '''Qolla s-Safra Battery''' ({{lang-mt|Batterija tal-Qolla s-Safra}})<ref>{{cite book|last1=de Boisgelin|first1=Louis|title=Ancient and Modern Malta: Containing a Full and Accurate Account of the Present State of the Islands of Malta and Goza, the History of the Knights of St. John of Jerusalem, Also a Narrative of the Events which Attended the Capture of These Islands by the French, and Their Conquest by the English: and an Appendix, Containing Authentic State Papers and Other Documents - Volume II|date=1805|publisher=Richard Phillips|location=[[London]]|page=192|url=https://books.google.com.mt/books?id=ZIU-AQAAMAAJ&pg=RA1-PA192#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref> or '''Gironda Battery''' ({{lang-mt|Batterija ta' Gironda}}),<ref>{{cite book|last1=Farrugia Randon|first1=Stanley|title=Heritage Saved – Din l-Art Ħelwa – 1965–2015|date=2015|publisher=Miller Distributors Ltd.|location=[[Luqa]]|isbn=9789995752132|page=119}}</ref> was an [[artillery battery]] in [[Marsalforn]], limits of [[Żebbuġ, Gozo|Żebbuġ]], [[Gozo]], [[Malta]]. It was built by the [[Knights Hospitaller|Order of Saint John]] in 1715 as one of a series of coastal fortifications around the Maltese Islands.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Zammit|first1=Vincent|title=The Order's 18th Century Fortifications|journal=Civilization|date=1984|volume=1|page=170|publisher=PEG Ltd|location=[[Ħamrun]]}}</ref>
The battery formed part of a chain of fortifications built to defend Marsalforn and nearby bays from Ottoman or Barbary attacks. Although the area was fortified by a number of [[Marsalforn Tower|towers]], batteries, redoubts and entrenchments, all of these have been destroyed except for [[Qolla l-Bajda Battery]] between Qbajjar and Xwejni Bays.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bezzina|first1=Joseph|title=Marsalforn Culture & History|url=http://www.zebbuggozo.com/history-marsalforn.php|website=Żebbuġ Local Council|accessdate=28 June 2015}}</ref>
The battery consisted of a semi-circular gun platform ringed by a parapet, and two blockhouses joined together by a wall. It has been demolished and no remains can be seen.
